stimulus:
Thank you for agreeing to participate in this study.

If during any part of the procedure you must stop for any reason, please inform the researcher that you do not wish to continue.

In this experiment, you will hear various words or sounds and see pictures of various animals and objects.

Most of the images will be of common everyday objects, such as cars, cats, cows, firearms, frogs, chickens, whistles, trains, motorcycles, and dogs.

Some of the images will be real-life stills, while others will be cartoons.

Sometimes, the word/sound will match the picture, for example you'll hear a meowing sound and see a cat.

Other times, the picture will not match the sound or word.

Your task is to decide as quickly as possible if the word/sound matches the picture or not.

For example, if you hear the word "cat" or hear a meowing sound, and then see a picture of a cat, you should press the MATCH key.

If the sound and image do not match, press the NOT-MATCH key to indicate that there is not a match.

If you make a mistake, you will hear a buzzing sound instead of a more pleasant sound.

Try to respond as quickly as possible, while making as few errors as possible. If you are making mistakes, you are probably rushing.

Please try to not move or blink your eyes during the presentation of the images. You can move and blink between images.

During the experiment there will be some breaks during which you can rest your eyes.
We will begin with 10 practice trials. Please let the experimenter know if you have any questions.

The rest of the experiment is divided into five blocks with 100 trials in each block. It will take about 45 minutes to complete.

The experimenter will be in the outer room and you can communicate with them through the monitor if you have any questions or wish to stop the experiment.

Remember, please try not to move or blink your eyes during the presentation of the images.

At the end of the experiment, we will show you your scores on the task so you can see how you did.

The experiment will start on the next screen.

Please take this opportunity to rest your eyes before proceeding.

When ready, press the enter key to continue to the next set of trials.
